<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(c) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Title services required in connection with assumptions.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 This is set forth in subparts A, B, and C of part 1965 of this chapter as appropriate for the loan type. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;&sect;1927.60&hyph;1927.61 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
[Reserved] 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;1927.62 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Voluntary conveyances. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
When a borrower offers to convey security, the approval official will process and close the transaction according
to &sect;1955.10 of subpart A of part 1955 of this chapter. The closing agent will issue a certification of title stating
that title is vested in the United States of America subject only to FmHA liens or prior liens previously approved by
FmHA in accordance with &sect;1955.10 of subpart A of part 1955 of this chapter. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;&sect;1927.63&hyph;1927.64 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
[Reserved] 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;1927.65 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Additional requirements in connection with loans to homestead entrymen, contract purchasers of farm units from
the Bureau of Reclamation, and certain American Indians. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Whenever loans or assumptions are subject to agreements with other agencies (e.g. loans to or assumptions by homestead
entrymen, American Indians, or contract purchasers from the Bureau of Reclamation), the title clearance and closing
of the transaction will be handled in accordance with special instructions issued by FmHA and/or other parties involved
applicable to the type of transaction, as well as those of this subpart. The special instructions may be in form of a
Memorandum of Understanding with the advice and approval of OGC. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;1927.66 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Cancellation of loan, assumption, or credit sale. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
If it is determined that the transaction will not be closed, the approval official will promptly notify the borrower
and the following parties who are involved in the case at the time the determination is made: the seller, attorney(s),
OGC, and the title company. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;&sect;1927.67&hyph;1927.89 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
[Reserved] 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;1927.90 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
State supplements. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The state supplement issued pursuant to this subpart will have prior National Office approval and will be the minimum
necessary to comply with state laws. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;1927.91 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Exception authority. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The Administrator may, in individual cases, make an exception to any requirement or provision of this subpart which
is not inconsistent with applicable law or opinion of the Comptroller General. The Administrator may exercise this
authority upon written request from the State Director or an Assistant Administrator provided the Administrator
determines that application of the requirement or provision would adversely affect the Government's interest.
Request for exception must be supported with documentation to explain adverse effect on the Government's interest,
proposed alternative courses of actions, and show how the adverse effect will be eliminated or minimized if the exception
is granted. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;&sect;1927.92&hyph;1927.99 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
[Reserved] 
