SUMMARY:
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=10 g=1 f=1 -->
 This document proposes the adoption of a new airworthiness directive 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(AD) that is applicable to certain British Aerospace Model ATP airplanes. This proposal 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
would require modification of the power supply for the communications system. This 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
proposal is prompted by reports of loss of power to the communications system due to an 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
electrical fault in the ground crew jack box or the handset of the public address (PA) 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
system. The actions specified by the proposed AD are intended to prevent the inability of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the flight crew to communicate with passengers via the PA system and with air traffic 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
control due to loss of power to the communication system, which may lead to unsafe 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
operation of the airplane. 
