These regulations are proposed under the Solid Waste Disposal Act (SWDA), as amended by the Hazardous and Solid Waste
Amendments of 1984 (HSWA). These statutes are commonly referred to as the Resource Conservation and Recovery Act
(RCRA) and are codified at Volume 42 of the United States Code (U.S.C.), sections 6901 to 6992k (42 U.S.C. 6901&hyph;6992k).

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Section 3001(a) of RCRA, 42 U.S.C. 6921(a), requires EPA to promulgate criteria for identifying characteristics
of hazardous wastes and for listing hazardous wastes. Section 3001(b) of RCRA requires EPA to promulgate regulations,
based on these criteria, identifying and listing hazardous wastes which shall be subject to the requirements of the
Act. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Hazardous waste is defined at section 1004(5) of RCRA, 42 U.S.C. 6903(5). There are two types of hazardous waste. First,
hazardous wastes are those solid wastes which may cause or significantly contribute to an increase in mortality,
serious irreversible illness, or incapacitating reversible illness. In addition, hazardous wastes are those solid
wastes which may pose a substantial present or potential hazard to human health or the environment when improperly
managed. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
EPA's regulations establishing criteria for listing hazardous wastes are codified at volume 40 of the Code of Federal
Regulations (CFR) &sect;261.11 (40 CFR 261.11). Section 261.11 states three criteria for identifying characteristics
and for listing wastes as hazardous. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->
</SUPPLEM>
<!-- PJG /STAG -->
</TEXT>
